'''Yamatsuteru Shrine''' (山津照神社, ''Yamatsuteru-jinja'') is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|en|神社}} located in {{ill|Maibara City|en|米原市}}, {{ill|Shiga Prefecture|en|滋賀県}}. It is a listed {{ill|Shikinai-sha|en|式内社}}, with its former shrine rank classified as a {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|en|県社}} under the modern shrine ranking system. The shrine's crest (''kamon'') features chrysanthemums and paulownias.

== Enshrined Deity ==
* {{ill|Kuninotokotachi no Mikoto|en|国常立尊}}

== History ==
The shrine's founding date is unknown. It is recorded in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyocho|en|延喜式神名帳}} as a listed shrine (''shikinai-sha'') and is said to enshrine a divided spirit from {{ill|Hoyama Shrine|en|帆山神社}} in {{ill|Echizen Province|en|越前国}}. Historical records state that the shrine was awarded the sixth rank (''Juroku-i'') in {{ill|Ninju|en|仁寿}} 1 (851 CE) and promoted to fourth rank (''Jushi-i'') in {{ill|Jogan|en|貞観}} 8 (866 CE).

In the {{ill|Meiji era|en|明治時代}}, the shrine was designated a {{ill|Village Shrine|en|郷社}} in 1881. It was later promoted to a {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|en|県社}} in 1921.

== Grounds ==
The shrine precincts include the {{ill|Yamatsuteru Shrine Kofun|en|山津照神社古墳}}, an ancient burial mound designated as a Shiga Prefectural Historic Site.
<gallery>
File:Yamatsuteru-jinja, honden-2.jpg|Honden
File:Yamatsuteru-jinja, honden-1.jpg|Chūmon (middle gate)
File:Yamatsuteru-jinja Kofun, funkyu-1.jpg|{{ill|Yamatsuteru Shrine Kofun|en|山津照神社古墳}} (Shiga Prefectural Historic Site)
File:Yamatsuteru-jinja, torii.jpg|Torii
</gallery>

== Associated Shrines ==
* {{ill|Aoki Shrine|en|青木神社}}
* {{ill|Wakamiya Hachiman Shrine|en|若宮八幡神社}}
* {{ill|Kasuga Shrine|en|春日社}}
* {{ill|Kitano Shrine|en|北野社}}

== Annual Rituals ==
* Annual Festival ({{ill|May 5|en|5月5日}})

== External Links ==
{{Commonscat|Yamatsuteru-jinja}}
