'''Yamatsuteru Shrine''' (山津照神社, ''Yamatsuteru-jinja'') is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Maibara, Shiga|Maibara City]], [[:en:Shiga Prefecture|Shiga Prefecture]]. It is a listed {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|lt=Shikinaisha}}, with its former shrine Rank classified as a {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|ja|県社|lt=Ken-sha|1=Modern_system_of_ranked_Shinto_shrines#Metropolitan_and_Prefectural_Shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=近代社格制度}} under the modern shrine Ranking system. The shrine's crest (''kamon'') features chrysanthemums and paulownias.

== deity ==
* [[:en:Kuni-no-Tokotachi|Kuninotokotachi no Mikoto]]

== History ==
The shrine's founding date is unknown. It is recorded in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} as a listed shrine (''shikinai-sha'') and is said to enshrine a divided spirit from {{ill|Hoyama Shrine|ja|帆山神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hoyama Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in [[:en:Echizen Province|Echizen Province]]. Historical records state that the shrine was awarded the sixth Rank (''Juroku-i'') in [[:en:Ninju|Ninju]] 1 (851 CE) and promoted to fourth Rank (''Jushi-i'') in [[:en:Zhenguan|Jogan]] 8 (866 CE).

In the [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji period]], the shrine was designated a {{ill|Village Shrine|ja|郷社|lt=Ken-sha|1=Modern_system_of_ranked_Shinto_shrines#District_shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Village Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=近代社格制度}} in 1881. It was later promoted to a {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|ja|県社|lt=Ken-sha|1=Modern_system_of_ranked_Shinto_shrines#Metropolitan_and_Prefectural_Shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=近代社格制度}} in 1921.

== Grounds ==
The shrine precincts include the {{ill|Yamatsuteru Shrine Kofun|ja|山津照神社古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamatsuteru Shrine Kofun|qq=}}, an ancient Kofun designated as a Shiga Prefectural Historic Site.
