'''Yamatsuteru Shrine''' (山津照神社, ''Yamatsuteru-jinja'') is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|en|Shinto shrine|WD=Q845945|lt=Shinto shrine|1=Shinto shrine}} located in {{ill|Maibara, Shiga|en|Maibara, Shiga|WD=Q824020|lt=Maibara City|1=Maibara, Shiga}}, {{ill|Shiga Prefecture|en|Shiga Prefecture|WD=Q131358|lt=Shiga Prefecture|1=Shiga Prefecture}}. It is a listed {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|1=Shikinaisha|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|lt=Shikinaisha}}, with its former shrine Rank classified as a {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|ja|県社|1=Ken-sha|WD=Q90139226}}{{efn|Ken-sha|WD=Q90139226|lt=Ken-sha|1=modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural Shrine|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=近代社格制度|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q712534}} under the modern shrine Ranking system. The shrine's crest (''kamon'') features chrysanthemums and paulownias.

== deity ==
* {{ill|Kuni-no-Tokotachi|en|Kuni-no-Tokotachi|WD=Q478504|lt=Kuninotokotachi no Mikoto|1=Kuni-no-Tokotachi}}

== History ==
The shrine's founding date is unknown. It is recorded in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} as a listed shrine (''shikinai-sha'') and is said to enshrine a divided spirit from {{ill|Hoyama Shrine|ja|帆山神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hoyama Shrine|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in {{ill|Echizen Province|en|Echizen Province|WD=Q1047144|lt=Echizen Province|1=Echizen Province}}. Historical records state that the shrine was awarded the sixth Rank (''Juroku-i'') in {{ill|Ninju|en|Ninju|WD=Q1373077|lt=Ninju|1=Ninju}} 1 (851 CE) and promoted to fourth Rank (''Jushi-i'') in {{ill|Zhenguan|en|Zhenguan|WD=Q3577278|lt=Jogan|1=Zhenguan}} 8 (866 CE).

In the {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|WD=Q3125096|lt=Meiji period|1=Meiji era}}, the shrine was designated a {{ill|Village Shrine|ja|郷社|1=Gō-sha|WD=Q134917316}}{{efn|District Shrines|WD=Q90139226|lt=Ken-sha|1=modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Village Shrine|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=近代社格制度|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q712534}} in 1881. It was later promoted to a {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|ja|県社|1=Ken-sha|WD=Q90139226}}{{efn|Ken-sha|WD=Q90139226|lt=Ken-sha|1=modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural Shrine|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=近代社格制度|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q712534}} in 1921.

== Grounds ==
The shrine precincts include the {{ill|Yamatsuteru Shrine Kofun|ja|山津照神社古墳|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamatsuteru Shrine Kofun|qq=}}, an ancient Kofun designated as a Shiga Prefectural Historic Site.
